INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass and the Governor to sign legislation banning the practice of “curative therapy,” also known as “reparative” or “conversion” therapy, or any attempt by a licensed professional to change, alter, or “correct” a minor’s sexual orientation.
EventItemMatterName: Banning the practice of “curative therapy,” also known as “reparative” or “conversion” therapy.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Veterans
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign H.R. 2638/S. 1109, known as the “Military Families Act,” which would allow the parents, children, and spouses of members of the Armed Forces to obtain lawful permanent residency and would abolish numerical limitations for immigrant visas for Filipino sons and daughters of parents who were naturalized under the Immigration Act of 1990.
EventItemMatterName: Military Families Act (H.R. 2638/S. 1109)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to oppose H.R. 1164, also known as the “National Language Act of 2011,” which would drastically reduce the ability of non-English speakers to meaningfully interact with their government and legal system by making English the official language of the United States.
EventItemMatterName: National Language Act of 2011 (H.R. 1164)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to permitting interested parties to receive notification of rulemaking and legislative actions.
EventItemMatterName: Permitting interested parties to receive notification of rulemaking and legislative actions.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Technology
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to notifying businesses when the city has received a complaint about its operation.
EventItemMatterName: Notifying businesses when the city has received a complaint about its operation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Transportation
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to permissible standing at fire hydrants.
EventItemMatterName: Permissible standing at fire hydrants.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Comptroller to grant shared authority to the New York City Comptroller for purposes of auditing the Metropolitan Transit Authority.
EventItemMatterName: NYS Comptroller for purposes of auditing the MTA.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to reporting on the disposal of ammunition shell casings.
EventItemMatterName: Reporting on the disposal of ammunition shell casings.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the Mayor of the City of New York to take necessary steps to ensure that ammunition casings generated by the City are disposed of in a way that neither perpetuates nor increases the threat of gun violence in New York City.
EventItemMatterName: Take necessary steps to ensure that ammunition casings generated by the City are disposed of in a way that neither perpetuates nor increases the threat of gun violence in NYC.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to distribution of the business owner’s bill of rights.
EventItemMatterName: Distribution of the business owner’s bill of rights.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Education
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the New York city charter, in relation to the establishment and development of school gardens.
EventItemMatterName: Establishment and development of school gardens.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon Governor Cuomo to maintain a moratorium on horizontal drilling and high volume hydraulic fracturing in New York State until additional studies have been drafted, reviewed and commented on by the public, and published.
EventItemMatterName: Governor Cuomo to maintain a moratorium on horizontal drilling and high volume hydraulic fracturing in NYS.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York in relation to the department of environmental protection imposing late fees and penalties.
EventItemMatterName: Department of environmental protection imposing late fees and penalties.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the publication of a brochure explaining the New York City property tax system.
EventItemMatterName: Publication of a brochure explaining the NYC property tax system.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the distribution of recycling outreach and education materials to residents by the department of sanitation.
EventItemMatterName: Distribution of recycling outreach and education materials to residents by the department of sanitation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Human Resources Administration to report information regarding its immigrant sponsor recoupment policy.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Human Resources Administration to report information regarding its immigrant sponsor recoupment policy.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Contracts
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to the publication of concept reports regarding requests for proposals.
EventItemMatterName: Publication of concept reports regarding requests for proposals.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on General Welfare
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to requiring the Department of Homeless Services to report information regarding veterans entering and exiting shelter.
EventItemMatterName: Requiring the Department of Homeless Services to report information regarding veterans entering and exiting shelter.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to amending the district plan of the Myrtle Avenue business improvement district to authorize additional services and modify existing services for the district.
EventItemMatterName: Myrtle Avenue BID

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Finance
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to amending the district plan of the Hub Third Avenue business improvement district to add services and capital improvements and modify existing services in the district, to change the method of assessment upon which the district charge is based and to increase the maximum total amount to be expended for improvements in the district.
EventItemMatterName: Hub Third Avenue BID

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Small Business
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the United States Congress to enact and the President to sign H.R. 4191, the Credit Union Small Business Lending Act.
EventItemMatterName: Credit Union Small Business Lending Act. (H.R. 4191)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Public Safety
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the New York State Assembly to pass A.10748, the New York State Senate to pass companion bill S.7254, and the Governor to sign such legislation, which would increase the penalty for assaulting a school crossing guard while on duty to a Class D felony of assault in the second degree.
EventItemMatterName: Increase the penalty for assaulting a school crossing guard while on duty to a Class D felony of assault in the second degree. (A.10748/S.7254)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Health
EventItemTitle: Resolution in support of S.5880-A/A.9018-A, which would amend the New York State Public Health Law by (i) designating tramadol as a schedule III narcotic drug, (ii) moving hydrocodone from the list of schedule III narcotic drugs to schedule II controlled substance to enhance existing penalties for possession or sale of large quantities of hydrocodone, and (iii) providing that certain compounds containing hydrocodone shall continue to be handled by licensed distributors in the manner applicable to schedule III controlled substances.
EventItemMatterName: Amend the New York State Public Health Law (S.5880-A/A.9018-A)

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Environmental Protection
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to filing semi-annual reports on catch basin cleanup and maintenance.
EventItemMatterName: Filling semi-annual reports on catch basin cleanup and maintenance.
